7:
Yaaagh! That's what you get for
disrespecting food!
10:
Who the hell do ya think you are
comin' into our hideout like you own
the place!
14:
And who do you think YOU are for
messing with the village?!
16:
While going about my business
looking for a way to get home, I
happened to pass by a rice farm...
18:
No thanks to you crooks, the farmers
were in no mood to be serving any
food!
21:
So you're with them! Then you'd
better behave yourself if ya hope to
see the hostages in one piece!
24:
We cleaned up nicely back there. Alk
and them are seein' to the captured
girls.
28:
Good timing! All that's left is to hand
these bandits over to the authorities!
36:
You saved not only our village but
our children as well! I don't know
how we can ever repay you!
38:
We only did what was right. No
thanks needed.
41:
Surely there must be something we
can do to show our gratitude!
44:
Um, I have an idea! Since you folks
specialize in rice...
47:
I'd be more than happy to try a few
of your rice balls!
52:
Mm! Rice balls are so much better
when the ingredients are fresh!
54:
I could eat these all day long! How
crazy is that?!
59: Is the rice really that different?
62:
You bet it is! You won't find rice this
sticky and sweet at your usual
restaurant!
67:
I know what you mean. It's definitely
different from Palpebra rice.
69:
To be fair though, I've tried some
really tasty varieties in other worlds
too.
71:
The rice here in Yamato is really
similar to what we have in
Landosol—which is my favorite.
75:
Heh, reminds me of how I
sometimes get a craving for
salamanders.
77:
I can stand my cravings for other
foods, but not Landosol rice balls.
Life's just not the same without
them...
80:
That's why I'm so happy with today's
treat!*nom nom*
87: You appear to be enjoying yourself.
90:
Sorry to keep you waiting! Here's an
extra batch of rice balls!
94:
Wow, this is a lot! Thank you so
much!
96:
Ahaha, that smile on your face
makes all the effort we put into
tending the rice fields worth it.
97: Please eat much as you'd like!
102:
Careful now... You could end up with
another situation in the village if she
interprets that too literally.
105:
Hey, I could really use an extra pair
of hands.
116:
Phew... What a satisfying meal that
was!
118:
They even gave us a few bags of
rice as a parting gift... I definitely
won't be going hungry anytime soon!
124:
Tell me, Pecorine. Did something
happen?
130:
I'm wondering because you're pretty
good at hiding things...
131:
And there was something off about
the way you acted when eating
those rice balls earlier.
134: But I could just be imagining things.
137:
Hrm... I guess there's no point trying
to pull the wool over your eyes, Alk!
140:
It's nothing major really. Eating
those rice balls and seeing that
family get along so well...
141:
It brought back memories of
Landosol... and my family.
144:
Thing is, even when I do get back
home, there won't be much of a
family reunion waiting for me.
Ahaha...
153:
The truth is my name and my family
have been taken from me...
154:
No one remembers me anymore...
To top it all off, I've been branded a
criminal.
161:
Haha... They took all they could from
me, but it wasn't ALL bad.
163:
Take my current name, Pecorine, for
instance. It's such a beautiful fit for
me, don't you think? Kokkoro came
up with it.
164:
Not to mention all the wonderful
friends I've made at the Gourmet
Guild... I've also met someone I really
care about...
166: As long as everyone's with me...
170:
I'm sure you'll get back what's
rightfully yours one day, Pecorine.
178:
Thank you so much, everyone. If you
don't mind me asking...
184: Heh... Do you even have to ask?
194:
Let's head back. Maybe you can
save some of that rice as a souvenir
for when you get back to the
Gourmet Guild.
200:
Right! Of course, I'll be sharing some
with you guys too!
